    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Corbin Carroll** serving as our undisputed anchor. With an elite score of 80.85, **Carroll** benefits from a strong park factor and a favorable matchup against Pop, but crucially, he maximizes his stolen base potential despite the opposition's decent catcher pop time. Joining him in the upper echelon are **Josh Naylor** (69.07) and **Trevor Story** (67.12). **Naylor** is primed to exploit Bolton\u2019s 4.57 xERA from the heart of the order, while **Story** is an intriguing play; despite a neutral platoon, the combination of a slow opposing delivery and favorable wind conditions creates a unique green light for his legs. **Mickey Moniak** also jumps into strong-start territory (64.99) thanks to a massive platoon advantage over Pivetta, which effectively mitigates the risk of a sub-optimal SP matchup.\n\nConversely, we are exercising caution with **James Wood** and **Seiya Suzuki**. While **Wood** occupies a prime leadoff spot, he faces the formidable Woodruff, dragging his efficiency score down to 51.65. **Suzuki** remains on the fringe at 49.75; while he benefits from favorable wind, the SP skill gap against Chandler is significant enough to suppress his overall outlook. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Zach McKinstry** (49.24). While his speed metrics\u2014specifically the 97% SB-friendly delivery rating\u2014made him a compelling target, his position in the bottom third of the lineup ultimately forced him to the bench in favor of the higher-projected efficiency of **Tyler Soderstrom**. \n\nWe are keeping a sharp eye on **Dalton Rushing**, whose 42.64 score is heavily suppressed by a daunting matchup against deGrom. While the wind helps, he is a \"start-only-if-necessary\" play today. Similarly, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** sits at 59.07, hovering just below our \"Strong\" tier, as the park factors and Rasmussen\u2019s stuff pose a legitimate ceiling on his scoring potential. We will monitor for any late-breaking lineup changes that might impact the base projections for **Vinnie Pasquantino** or **Austin Riley**, but for now, the roster is set to maximize our speed-weighted scoring needs while managing our limited daily game caps.",
